                                    <list>
                                        <item>
                                            <p>Paper, about 12 1/8 in. by 6 7/8 , consisting of 42
                                                leaves (Add. 14,726, foll. 87—128), of which the
                                                last is slightly torn. The quires, four in number,
                                                are signed with letters. There are from 34 to 38
                                                lines in each page. This manuscript is written in a
                                                good, regular hand, apparently of the xth cent.</p>
